;; Real, dated, git-verified input facts for the cloud-itonami GitHub-to-west
;; registration pipeline, modeled as an XMILE (OASIS 1.0) stock-flow system
;; via kotoba-lang/org-oasis-open-xmile. See
;; src/loop_system_dynamics/cloud_itonami_xmile.cljs for how this is turned
;; into stocks/flows and simulated.
;;
;; Backlog_<cat> (stock) = github-total - west-registered-t1 (repos that
;;   exist on GitHub but are not yet in com-junkawasaki/root's manifest/west.yml).
;; Reg_<cat> rate (flow, repos/day) = (west-registered-t1 - west-registered-t0)
;;   / days -- a REAL observed average over a REAL dated window, not a guess.
;;   A category with zero registration events in the window (isco, iso,
;;   unspsc, cofog, gtin, regulatory, partners, jsic, hygiene) gets rate 0 --
;;   a measured zero, per dynamics.core's no-fabrication convention (never
;;   defaulted, always explicitly checked against both snapshots).
{:as-of "2026-07-21"

 :window
 {:t0 "2026-07-19T21:02:53+09:00"
  :t0-source "com-junkawasaki/root git commit fc6c7ec3bfb7d3026fd23f7ccc799bfa711f4fb8 (oldest commit in local shallow clone history at observation time), manifest/west.yml as of that commit"
  :t1 "2026-07-21T10:42:32+09:00"
  :t1-source "com-junkawasaki/root git commit 46e9386d420 (HEAD at observation time), manifest/west.yml"
  :days 1.5692
  :note "window is bounded by local shallow-clone depth (237 commits), not by when registration activity actually started -- a wider window would need `git fetch --deepen` per com-junkawasaki/root CLAUDE.md's targeted-depth guidance. Org-wide GitHub repo total was independently re-confirmed unchanged (1331) at both 2026-07-20 (entities-seed.edn) and 2026-07-21 (this file's own `gh api` call), so all of `west-registered`'s movement in the window is genuine catch-up registration, not new repo creation diluting the count."}

